[Rabies has a variable incubation period in human beings ranging from
relatively short to quite long. Since the womans parents are present,
perhaps some information regarding possible exposure to rabies may be
gained which may be useful for diagnosis.
The article does not indicate the clinical signs/symptoms in this case, nor
does it indicate potential exposure to a rabid animal. Consequently, this
may yet turn out to be another disease. ­ Mod.TG
